@startuml
' @id(DOM-FONT-DATABASE)
' Current-side domain concept now present in code: the font database the
' SVG rasterizer depends on, populated once by shared_fontdb() and passed
' into usvg::Options. Closes the objective-only parity gap.
title Font database for SVG rasterization (current)

class SvgRasterizer {
  + parse_intrinsic_size(bytes) : Vec2
  + rebuild(ctx, zoom) : Result
}

class FontDatabase {
  + fontCount : int
  + defaultFamily : String
  + loadSystemFonts() : void
}

SvgRasterizer "1" o-- "1" FontDatabase : resolves <text> via >

note bottom of FontDatabase
  Backed by usvg::fontdb::Database. Built once
  in shared_fontdb() (static OnceLock), filled
  by load_system_fonts(), then Arc-cloned into
  usvg::Options.fontdb at every parse site.
  defaultFamily = usvg default ("Times New Roman").
end note
@enduml
